I liked the concept a lot: The adventure vendors are located ina central place (EC tunnel and on the Everfrost frozen river), and you get to them to get assigned an adventure. Back then, groups had to be 4 members, at least, to get an assignment. You have 30 minutes to get to the location of the dungeon - I think there are several dungeon entrances, depending on the adventure you get. The orcs entrance was in SRo, while the one in everfrost was very close to the adventure vendors there, so it varies.<br>
You then have 90 minutes to complete the assignment - we failed in both cases. Scouting is important, you don't have enough time to clear the whole thing. Those dungeons are pretty big. They are also trapped, so scouting isn't too simple. And the architecture and scenery was great. I missed a passage in the menagerie even, due to optical illusion like effects - placing of walls and coloring - I find that very cool.<br>
<br>
Fights were challenging but not overly so. But as I said, you don't get to clear the whole thing. The orcs in the hills are very mean looking. Some of the monsters in the menagerie looked like the ones in PoTorment, while two or three models were totally new (and very cool). <br>
<br>
Rewards and loot weren't in place, so I can't comment on those.<br>
All in all, I think it's a very fun expansion - dungeon crawling at it's best <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95331" target="_new">
<img border=0 src="http://www.tshrew.net/saga/bippin/BippinSig-3.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nysaan>Nysaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/5/03 3:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1898.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LDoN Beta Testers: Spill your guts! NDA is lifted.</span><hr size=1> Hehe I have already &quot;spilt my guts&quot; on three other boards today.  I'm out of LDoN energy right now.  It rocks, though.  If nobody else covers everything, I will try to add comments later on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START  >D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/grin.gif ALT=" >D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buvin>Buvin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>the ever dying ranger</span><br>  Posts: 362<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/6/03 6:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1898.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: LDoN Beta Testers: Spill your guts! NDA is lifted.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?threadid=27980">Nice LDoN write up on the Ranger's Glade.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~mcjohnson/images/EQ/sig55.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
