<br>
Caveat - I only tried one crawl in the beta, as a 65 SK, with a 65 enchanter and cleric for company.  But I found it frustrating - I ran out of mana to snare, didn't have time to sit and get more, no time to debate which way to go, no time to chat, just rush rush rush.  That's not the EQ I enjoy, and I don't see how it would continue to be interesting after the first few times.  The concept sounded fun but I found it to be just a race against the clock in disposable zones you'll never see again.  I'm sure it will be great for getting neat loot.  And for lvl 65 players who want a 90 minute AAXP grind and have trouble finding anything blue to hunt in 'normal' zones.  And I really can see no other interest.<br>
<br>
It's fun to get way into the depths of some famous zone and learn your way around.  &quot;Wow, we got a group of 6 down to the royals in Chardok!!&quot;  With disposable zones, that enjoyment is gone.  &quot;Hey ... we battled our way all the way down to ... some zone that doesn't exist any more ... and nobody will ever see again ... and I have no idea what it looked like ...&quot;  Ooh, aah, yawn.  <br>
<br>
I was also playing with experienced players.  I wouldn't say we were the best of the best, but we were pretty knowledgeable of our classes and how to play.  Yet we didn't complete our dungeon in the time limit.  I cannot possibly imagine how an inexperienced or even average group would find this anything approaching possible.<br>
<br>
Conclusion:  I went in thinking it would be really neat, and thinking this expansion sounds great.  I came out thinking I'd just participated in one rushed 90 minute grind, and decided I won't bother buying the expansion. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
