The dungeons are made for <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>crawls</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, not 'exp grinding'.<br>
I've found them very exciting so far, the time limit gives you a reason to press on and to conserve mana etc, it adds a new element of tactics, we had some really spectacular fights yesterday, where every group members contribution counted.<br>
<br>
The adventures are hard enough to give you a real feeling of accomplishment, should you complete your objective. You often don't HAVE to kill everything in a dungeon to complete a mission and sometimes you can't if you want to finish in time, wich adds a new tactical element - you have to make quick desicions because you never know what to expect and if you make the wrong desicion you'll just have to make the best of it.<br>
<br>
Rogues are REALLY useful now, the traps are really, really bad hehe, a single trap wiped out my whole group in less than a minute, it was a poison AoE DoT that was MUCH more powerful than for example Trakanon's, if your lockpicks fail...BOOM <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
The time limit gives you a challenge, but it also guarantees that a member can leave/log when the time is up - No corpse recoveries for hours afterwards. By the way, if you die it's easy to get back, nothing respawns.<br>
<br>
This is going to make EQ a lot of fun again for me for a long time, i was getting a bit tired of the same hunting procedures year after year. LDoN is what i was missing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
